# Do's and Don'ts

## Do's

### Do Practice Regularly

Linux skills improve through repetition and daily use.

### Do Read Command Output Carefully

Many mistakes occur because users execute commands without reviewing the output.

### Do Use the Manual Pages

Learn to use:

man <command>

Example:

man ls

### Do Keep Notes

Document commands, observations, and lessons learned while practicing.

### Do Understand Before Memorizing

Focus on understanding what a command does rather than simply memorizing syntax.

---

## Don'ts

### Don't Run Commands You Don't Understand

Research commands before executing them.

### Don't Use sudo Unnecessarily

Only elevate privileges when required.

### Don't Delete Files Without Verifying

Always confirm the file path before using:

rm

or

rm -rf

### Don't Ignore Error Messages

Error messages often provide useful troubleshooting information.

### Don't Depend Entirely on Copy-and-Paste

Typing commands manually helps build familiarity and confidence.

